<LegalLayout title="Cookie Policy (UK)" effectiveDate="1 September 2024">
    <p>Autoflow Solutions UK uses cookies to enhance your browsing experience. This Cookie Policy explains what cookies are, how we use them, and how you can control their use in compliance with the Privacy and Electronic Communications Regulations (PECR).</p>

    <h2>What Are Cookies?</h2>
    <p>Cookies are small text files that are stored on your device when you visit a website. They help websites remember your preferences and improve user experience.</p>

    <h2>Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> These cookies are necessary for the website to function correctly. Without these cookies, certain features (like navigation and form submission) would not be possible.</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> We use these cookies to understand how visitors in the UK interact with our website, helping us improve content and performance. These may include cookies from third-party analytics services like Google Analytics.</li>
        <li><strong>Functional Cookies:</strong> These cookies remember your preferences, such as regional settings (UK) to provide a more personalized experience.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Managing Cookies</h2>
    <p>You can choose to accept or reject cookies by adjusting your browser settings. In the UK, you have the right to give informed consent for non-essential cookies. Please note that blocking cookies may affect your ability to use certain features of our website.</p>

    <h2>Third-Party Cookies</h2>
    <p>Some cookies may be placed by third-party services that appear on our site, such as social media sharing buttons. We do not control the use of these cookies, and their usage is subject to the privacy policies of the respective providers. If you have any concerns or questions about our use of cookies, contact us at <a href="mailto:info@autoflow-solutions.com">info@autoflow-solutions.com</a>.</p>
</LegalLayout>
